k <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set covered Varoma aside on a plate to keep warm."},{"content":"Add cream to mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and blend <b>2 min\/speed 5<b>-<strong>10, increasing speed gradually.<\/strong> Serve soup for starter (see tip), then salmon fillets and broccoli for main course."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If the celery stalks have leaves, place a few leaves on top of salmon fillets before steaming to add extra flavour.","For a milder taste omit drizzling salmon with marinade in <b>step 3<b>.","After serving the soup, set mixing bowl and covered Varoma back in position so the main course keeps warm while the soup is enjoyed.","A quick, healthy meal with bright flavours and colours, starting with a vibrant green pea soup with zingy ginger, followed by lemon-marinated salmon with steamed broccoli: this recipe can turn a weeknight dinner into a special treat."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","50m","4 portions"]}